    "content": "【PPT 03 结构图】\n\n【教师台词】\"There are three types of phrases. Let's learn them one by one.\"\n\n★ NP — Noun Phrase 名词短语\n▲ 板书：NP = (限定词) + (副词) + 形容词 + 核心名词\n例：a really big challenge\n    the school adviser\n    my best friend\n\n【教师台词】\"The core is a NOUN. Everything else modifies it. What can come before a noun? Articles (a/the), adjectives (big, happy), adverbs (really, very).\"\n\n★ AdjP — Adjective Phrase 形容词短语\n▲ 板书：AdjP = (副词) + 核心形容词\n例：very confused\n    quite difficult\n    really happy\n\n【教师台词】\"The core is an ADJECTIVE. An adverb can make it stronger or weaker. 'Very confused' is stronger than just 'confused'. 'Quite difficult' is softer than 'very difficult'.\"\n\n★ AdvP — Adverb Phrase 副词短语\n▲ 板书：AdvP = (副词) + 核心副词\n例：very quickly\n    quite well\n    really hard\n\n【教师台词】\"The core is an ADVERB. Yes, an adverb can modify another adverb! 'Very quickly' — 'very' tells us HOW quickly.\"\n\n【易错点提醒】学生可能问：\"老师，really 是副词但它在 a really big challenge 里修饰 big，不是修饰 challenge。\" 回答：\"Exactly! Really 修饰 big（形容词），整个 really big 再修饰 challenge（名词）。短语可以嵌套！\" 这个点A班可以展开，B班略过。"
