    "content": "【PPT 02 课文原句对比】\n\n【教师台词】\"Last lesson we read about the Aswan Dam. Today we look at the grammar in that text. Look at these two groups of sentences. They describe the SAME thing, but in different ways. What's different? Talk to your partner.\"\n\n▲ PPT展示3组对比句：\n\n| Group A (Informal) | Group B (Formal) |\n|---|---|\n| 1a. The temple which they talked about was saved. | 1b. The temple about which they talked was saved. |\n| 2a. The countries which Egypt turned to for help. | 2b. The countries to which Egypt turned for help. |\n| 3a. The experts whom they worked with came from 50 countries. | 3b. The experts with whom they worked came from 50 countries. |\n\n【预设回答】\n- \"In B, the preposition (about/to/with) moved to the front, before which/whom.\"（教师：\"Excellent observation!\"）\n- \"B uses 'whom' instead of 'who'.\"（教师：\"Good catch! After a preposition, we use 'whom' for people, not 'who'.\"）\n- B班可能只看到\"介词位置变了\"——教师追问：\"Which preposition? About, to, with. Where did they come from?\" 引导学生发现介词来自动词搭配。\n\n【板书时机】教师在黑板中央写下对比示例：\n  Informal: ...which they talked ABOUT\n  Formal:   ...ABOUT WHICH they talked\n\n【教师台词】\"Why do we need this formal version? In academic writing, news reports, and formal speeches, we move the preposition to the front. It sounds more professional. Today we'll learn how to do this.\""
