  "exercises": "【基础作业】（全体必做）\nI. 根据句意和首字母提示完成句子：\n1. The Tibetan a______ lives on the high plateau at 5,000 meters.\n2. In the 1990s, hunters killed them for their wool, making them e______.\n3. The government established a nature r______ to protect them.\n4. Thanks to protection efforts, the population has r______ to 150,000.\n5. Buying products made from endangered species is i______.\n\nII. 用方框中短语的正确形式填空（adapt to / exist in harmony / be removed from / drop to / recover from）：\n6. The antelopes had to ______ the harsh environment of the plateau.\n7. The population ______ fewer than 50,000 due to illegal hunting.\n8. In 2016, the antelope was ______ the endangered species list.\n9. We must learn to ______ with nature.\n\n【提高作业】（A班必做，B班选做）\nIII. 写一段50词短文，介绍另一种中国濒危动物（如大熊猫、金丝猴、雪豹），至少使用3个本课核心词汇。\n\n【参考答案——教师用】\nI. 1. antelope  2. endangered  3. reserve  4. recovered  5. illegal\nII. 6. adapt to  7. dropped to  8. removed from  9. exist in harmony\nIII. 评分标准：①内容相关②词汇使用③语法正确④字数50词左右。示例：The giant panda was once endangered due to habitat loss. The government established reserves and banned illegal logging. Now the population has recovered to over 1,800. In 2016, it was removed from the endangered list. (38 words)",
