    "content": "【PPT 03 规则归纳表】\n\n【教师台词】\"When do we use the passive voice? Three situations:\"\n\n① 不知道谁在做：\n  \"The forest is being destroyed.\" (We don't know who is cutting the trees.)\n  \n② 强调承受者：\n  \"Antelopes are being protected.\" (We care about the antelopes, not who is protecting them.)\n  \n③ 执行者显而易见或不想提及：\n  \"New laws are being made.\" (Obviously by the government — no need to say.)\n\n【教师台词】\"Now, important rule: NOT all verbs can be passive! Only TRANSITIVE verbs (及物动词 — verbs with an object). 'Kill' can be passive (something is being killed). But 'happen' CANNOT — you can't say 'something is being happened.' Why? Because 'happen' has no object.\"\n\n【易错点提醒】\n①常见不及物动词（不能被动）：happen, occur, exist, appear, disappear, rise, fall\n②\"being\"不可省略：✗ \"are protected\" → ✓ \"are being protected\"（此刻正在被保护）\n③be动词随主语：The antelopes ARE being protected. / The antelope IS being protected.\n\n【板书时机】在规则表下方补充：\n  ✗ happen → is being happened (错误！)\n  ✓ destroy → is being destroyed (正确)\n  ✓ protect → is being protected (正确)"
