    "content": "【PPT 04 主动转被动练习（5题）】\n\n【教师台词】\"Convert these active sentences to passive. Remember: 3 steps — ① find the object (it becomes the new subject) ② add am/is/are + being ③ change the main verb to V3.\"\n\n1. Illegal hunters are killing Tibetan antelopes for their wool.\n2. The government is building new nature reserves.\n3. Scientists are tracking the antelope population.\n4. Volunteers are cleaning up the habitat.\n5. Poachers are selling shahtoosh shawls online.\n\n▲ 学生独立完成5分钟。教师巡视。\n\n【预设答案】\n1. Tibetan antelopes ARE BEING KILLED for their wool (by illegal hunters).\n2. New nature reserves ARE BEING BUILT (by the government).\n3. The antelope population IS BEING TRACKED (by scientists).\n4. The habitat IS BEING CLEANED UP (by volunteers).\n5. Shahtoosh shawls ARE BEING SOLD online (by poachers).\n\n【易错点提醒】①第3题 population 是单数 → IS being tracked（学生容易写ARE）；②第4题 clean up → cleaned up（up是小品词，跟过去分词一起放）；③第5题 sell → sold（不规则变化）。\n\n【PPT 05 填空练习（5题）】\n\n【教师台词】\"Now fill in the blanks with the present continuous passive form.\"\n\n1. The antelopes ______ (protect) by rangers in the reserve.\n2. Their habitat ______ (destroy) by human activities.\n3. New laws ______ (make) to stop illegal hunting.\n4. The population ______ (monitor) by scientists.\n5. Shahtoosh shawls ______ (sell) in the black market.\n\n【预设答案】\n1. are being protected\n2. is being destroyed\n3. are being made\n4. is being monitored\n5. are being sold\n\n【差异化提示】A班可增加口语练习：用现在进行时被动描述一个正在进行的环保行动。B班重点确保being不遗漏。"
