    "content": "【PPT 04 V-ing vs. V3辨析练习（6对）】\n\n【教师台词】\"Choose V-ing or V3 for each sentence.\"\n\n1. The ______ (fall) leaves covered the ground. → fallen (已经落下的)\n2. The ______ (develop) countries should help the ______ (develop) countries. → developed / developing\n3. The book ______ (write) by this author is famous. → written (书被写)\n4. The boy ______ (stand) by the door is my brother. → standing (男孩主动站)\n5. The language ______ (speak) in Wales is Welsh. → spoken (语言被说)\n6. The ______ (excite) children ran to the playground. → excited (孩子们被激发)\n\n【PPT 05 have sth. done练习（5题）】\n\n【教师台词】\"Rewrite using 'have sth. done'.\"\n\n1. A mechanic repaired my car. → I had my car repaired.\n2. A tailor made her dress. → She had her dress made.\n3. Someone stole his wallet. → He had his wallet stolen.\n4. A dentist checked my teeth. → I had my teeth checked.\n5. A builder renovated their house. → They had their house renovated.\n\n【易错点提醒】第3题\"had his wallet stolen\"是被动遭遇——不是他主动让人偷钱包！这是have sth. done的\"遭遇\"用法。\n\n【PPT 06 课文语境填空（5题）】\n\n1. The roads ______ (build) by the Romans are still visible today. → built\n2. The ______ (unite) Kingdom was formed over centuries. → United\n3. The legal system ______ (introduce) by the Normans still exists. → introduced\n4. Visitors can have their photos ______ (take) at the castle. → taken\n5. The ______ (write) records show evidence of Roman civilization. → written\n\n【差异化提示】A班可增加自由造句；B班重点掌握V-ing/V3的主动/被动判断。"
