    "content": "【PPT 02 从句vs. V3短语对比】\n\n【教师台词】\"Last lesson we read about Eric and the virtual choir. Today let's look at the grammar. Compare these pairs — same meaning, different form:\"\n\n| 从句版本（长） | V3短语版本（短） |\n|---|---|\n| Because he was inspired by the video, Eric created the choir. | Inspired by the video, Eric created the choir. |\n| When it is seen from above, the choir looks like a mosaic. | Seen from above, the choir looks like a mosaic. |\n| Although she was tired, the singer performed beautifully. | Although tired, the singer performed beautifully. |\n\n【教师台词】\"What disappeared in the V3 versions? What stayed? Talk to your partner.\"\n\n【预设回答】\n- \"The subject and 'be' verb disappeared.\" (教师：\"Right! 'He was' → gone. 'It is' → gone.\"）\n- \"The past participle stayed.\" (教师：\"Yes! Inspired, seen, tired — all V3.\"）\n- \"It's shorter but means the same.\" (教师：\"Exactly! This is how you make your writing more CONCISE.\"）\n\n【板书时机——双色粉笔构建规则】\n\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│   PAST PARTICIPLE (V3) AS ADVERBIAL                 │\n│                                                    │\n│   从句：[Subject] + be + V3, [Main Clause]         │\n│   V3：  V3 (phrase), [Main Clause]                 │\n│                                                    │\n│   消失：主语 + be动词                                │\n│   保留：V3（过去分词）                               │\n│                                                    │\n│   效果：更简洁、更高级                                │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘"
