  "blackboard": "┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│        PAST PARTICIPLE (V3) AS ADVERBIAL                  │\n├───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                           │\n│  从句：[Subject] + be + V3, [Main Clause]                 │\n│  V3：  V3 (phrase), [Main Clause]                         │\n│  → 消失：主语+be  保留：V3                                │\n│                                                           │\n│  四种逻辑关系：                                            │\n│  ① 原因 (Because): Inspired by..., Eric...               │\n│  ② 时间 (When): Seen from above, the choir...            │\n│  ③ 条件 (If): Given more time, they...                   │\n│  ④ 让步 (Though): Though tired, the singer...            │\n│                                                           │\n│  ⚠ 逻辑主语一致性：V3主语 = 主句主语                      │\n│    ✓ Inspired by the video, Eric created...              │\n│    ✗ Inspired by the video, the choir was created...     │\n│                                                           │\n│  V3 (被动) vs. V-ing (主动)：                              │\n│  主语RECEIVE→V3   主语DO→V-ing                            │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘",
  "exercises": "【基础作业】（全体必做）\nI. 将下列状语从句简化为V3短语：\n1. Because he was encouraged by the response, Eric started VC2.\n2. When it is viewed online, the virtual choir is amazing.\n3. Although she was exhausted, the singer performed well.\n4. If they are given internet access, anyone can join.\n5. Because they were moved by the music, the audience stood up.\n\nII. 选择V3或V-ing填空：\n6. ______ (inspire) by the music, she composed a song. → Inspired\n7. ______ (perform) on stage, he felt alive. → Performing\n8. ______ (move) by the story, they decided to help. → Moved\n9. ______ (see) from a distance, the choir looked beautiful. → Seen\n10. ______ (sing) together, the choir sounded powerful. → Singing\n\n【提高作业】（A班必做，B班选做）\nIII. 写3个句子，描述一次音乐体验，使用V3作状语。确保逻辑主语一致。\n\n【参考答案——教师用】\nI. 1. Encouraged by the response, Eric started VC2.\n   2. Viewed online, the virtual choir is amazing.\n   3. Though exhausted, the singer performed well.\n   4. Given internet access, anyone can join.\n   5. Moved by the music, the audience stood up.\nII. 6. Inspired  7. Performing  8. Moved  9. Seen  10. Singing\nIII. 评分标准：①V3使用正确②逻辑主语一致③内容相关。示例：Inspired by the concert, I started learning guitar. Moved by the lyrics, I cried. Given a chance to perform, I would sing my favorite song.",
  "reflection": "✅ 亮点：从句vs. V3短语对比直观，学生能自主发现\"主语+be消失\"的规律；逻辑主语一致性的正误对比（Eric vs. the choir）效果显著；V3/V-ing选择规则清晰。\n\n⚠️ 需改进：逻辑主语一致性是最大难点，部分学生在造句时仍会写出悬垂分词；四种逻辑关系（原因/时间/条件/让步）的区分需要更多语境练习。\n\n📌 下节课衔接：写作课的演讲稿中要求使用V3作状语（\"Inspired by..., I...\"），实现语法向写作的最终迁移。",
